        <h2>How Our Technicians Repair a Bosch Cooktop</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="process-grid">
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <h3>Platform-Specific Diagnosis First</h3>
          <p>Gas, induction, and electric glass-top have different
          diagnostic trees. We start by confirming the platform and
          identifying whether the failure is in the heating system, the
          controls, or the glass panel. Saves time, avoids wrong-platform
          fixes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <h3>Cookware Test Before Induction Parts</h3>
          <p>Before quoting a $440 zone inverter on an induction
          "no-heat" call, we verify cookware compatibility with the magnet
          test. Saves owners hundreds when the issue is just the pan, not
          the cooktop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <h3>Test Every Electrical Component Before Swap</h3>
          <p>Meter the spark module before replacing. Test touch panel
          capacitance before ordering replacement. Verify radiant element
          continuity. Bosch parts aren't cheap — no throwing money at
          wrong components.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <h3>Manufacturer-Approved Parts Only</h3>
          <p>Aftermarket spark modules fail within 12 months. Aftermarket
          touch panels drift out of calibration. Aftermarket replacement
          glass doesn't seat in the cutout correctly. We install Bosch
          manufacturer-approved parts only.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
          <h3>Address the Cause, Not Just the Failure</h3>
          <p>A burner cap that keeps misaligning points to cleaning
          technique. Recurring spark failures on one burner point to grease
          migration. A cracked glass panel points to cookware drop habits.
          We fix the visible problem and flag the root cause.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">6</div>
          <h3>Full Function Test Before We Leave</h3>
          <p>Every burner lit and cycled through heat settings on gas.
          Every zone activated and tested on induction. Every radiant
          element cycled through infinite switch positions on electric.
          90-day labor warranty, 1-year warranty on installed parts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

